 Secretary of AFN, Elijah Adamu, said in Lagos that the trials would hold from at the Moshood Abiola National Stadium, Abuja (Formerly Abuja National Stadium). Photo/twitter/BashirAhmad  The Secretary of AFN, Elijah Adamu, said in Lagos that the trials would hold from June 24 to June 27, at the Moshood Abiola National Stadium, Abuja. Adamu said that the arrival date was June 24 , while June 25 to June 26 would be the competition days and that participants were to depart on June 27. “The states with eligible athletes are to send their entries to ngr@mf.iaaf.org or abgiwa@aol.com on or before June 21,” he said a statement. Adamu added that 2019 affiliation fees was one of the requirements for participation, saying that those with outstanding fees should ensure they paid. The African Games is scheduled for Aug. 19 to Aug. 31, in Rabat, Morocco.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .